RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 97. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH PROPHET away quickly and stalked an outside pair into the first turn, went up to challenge around the bend, gained the lead and moved clear, showed the way under confident handling on the far turn, asked right handed in upper stretch and widened while ridden out late. ADMIRALTY PLACE (GB) broke a step slow, reserved inside early, lacked room when boxed in on the far turn then tipped between rivals and entered the lane two wide, angled out in the lane and produced a mild rally to best the rest. RIDLEY'S MAJOR stalked in the two path then between rivals, exited the backstretch three deep, rounded the far turn four then five wide and gained the show. DANCING RINCA bumped leaving the gate, tracked three wide early, moved up four deep leaving the backstretch, shifted in and bumped rival while still four deep on the far turn, moved in some entering the stretch and flattened to fourth. THIRTY FOUR COUPE had to steady twice before the first turn, stalked along the inside, saved ground to the stretch and flattened out. PALAGIO was off slow in the beginning, settled outside a rival near the back, rounded the far turn in the three path, moved out in the stretch and improved position. WARRIOR ROAD bumped leaving the gate, showed early speed but drifted out a bit while rank on the first turn, ceded command and chased up the backstretch, got brushed between rivals on the far turn and weakened in the lane. OVERRULE had to steady behind a rival early, was a bit rank early along the rail, started the far turn in the two path then moved inside and failed to menace, then walked into the van following the race. CUPID'S CRUSADER showed speed then became rank and drifted into the first turn, stalked the speed three deep, got bumped between rivals on the far turn and faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 26000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, For Each $1,750 To $12,500 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROMAN EMPRESS stalked the pace from the inside, tipped two wide and between foes with a quarter mile left to run, challenged PARCO from inside in upper stretch, put a head in front at the eighth pole, dueled with AWESOME PAMELA in deep stretch and gamely prevailed. AWESOME PAMELA trailed two wide into the first turn, moved closer to stalk the top pair from between rivals on the backstretch, eased out to the three path late on the far turn, launched a bid from outside in upper stretch, fought with ROMAN EMPRESS in the final sixteenth but could not get by. PARCO raced up close outside the leader into the first turn then chased into the backstretch, drew alongside again to duel for command, put away NAUGHTY EVELYN nearing the quarter pole, was overtaken with a furlong remaining and flattened to third. NAUGHTY EVELYN sped to the front from inside, dueled with PARCO up the backstretch, lost command and could not keep up with that rival nearing the quarter pole and weakened down the lane. SHEMAKESCENTS chased three wide around both turns, raced four wide into the stretch and came up empty.

MAGIC CAPITAL bumped at the start and dropped back, trailed along the rail into the turn, angled out and came five wide into the stretch and was along for the show. RACE.FOOTNOTES: GENERAL MATHIS broke in and bumped rival, unhurried in the beginning near the inside then shifted to the two path, angled out on the far turn and came five wide into the stretch, closed fast from outside and edged DERECHO DANDY in the final jumps. DERECHO DANDY set the pace outside SO I'M TOLD early, raced on even terms past the half-mile pole, fought through the far turn and into the lane, put away inner rival with a sixteenth remaining but got nailed at the wire. CIRCLEOFCHAMPIONS took a bumped at the start, stalked the pace on the inside, coaxed along around the far turn, tipped out in upper stretch and finished willingly for the show honors. SO I'M TOLD stumbled leaving the gate, prompted the pace along the inside, moved up to duel on the backstretch, battled through the far turn and into the stretch, fought to the eighth pole then flattened in deep stretch. CAISSON sat off the pace and steered to the inside, took closer order leaving the backstretch, tipped off the rail while finding some traffic on the far turn, lost his path and had to steady in upper stretch and could not regain the needed momentum. FLINT STROLL tracked the speed in the two path, got blocked on the far turn while three deep, angled to the two path leaving that bend and failed to threaten. BIRTH OF COOL stalked the pace from between rivals, took aim at the leaders two wide into the stretch, moved out in the lane and weakened. CHICKASAW was off slow to begin, reserved in the early going, traveled on the inside, angled out on the far turn and top of the lane and failed to menace. OCULUS stalked the top pair three deep and weakened.
